你应该限制糖的摄入量。
医生建议减少盐的摄入。

bilingual.source: I count my calories intake every day.
bilingual.target: 我每天计算我摄入的卡路里。
医生建议减少嘌呤的摄入。

bilingual.source: Excessive sugar intake is harmful to health.
bilingual.target: 过多的糖摄入对健康有害。

bilingual.source: Excessive salt intake is harmful to health.
bilingual.target: 过多的食盐摄入对健康有害。

bilingual.source: She tracks her calories intake every day.
bilingual.target: 她每天记录她的卡路里摄入量。

bilingual.source: The doctor advised reducing the intake of lipin.
bilingual.target: 医生建议减少脂质的摄入。

bilingual.source: The doctor advised him to reduce his fat intake.
bilingual.target: 医生建议他减少脂肪摄入。

yingyinNormal.en: Certainly. It's not like I have to moderate my food intake because I'm planning on eating again very shortly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当然，我又没有因为很快要吃第二餐而故意限制食物摄入量。

yingyinNormal.en: You need to increase your spider intake, so he'll be able to climb ceilings properly. And eat lots of sheep bile.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你需要增加蜘蛛的摄入量，那么他就可以有能力爬上天花板了，还有多吃羊胆汁。

yingyinNormal.en: Alright. Well, how long will it take to free swim from the intake to the service hatch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，从进水口自由潜泳到服务舱门需要多长时间。

yingyinNormal.en: Where does the water come from? Desalinized seawater flows through the intake. In the pipeline.
yingyinNormal.zh: 水流来自哪里？由进水口引入的淡化海水,储备在这个管道中。

yingyinNormal.en: Meaning after 3 days of the recommended daily water intake, you'd have burned off that 200 calories.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也就是说，三天后，就可以燃烧那200卡路里。

yingyinNormal.en: And before you ask. The system is designed to shut down automatically if any metal enters the intake. No oxygen tanks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 顺便告诉你，如果检测到任何金属物体进入进水口，系统就会自动关闭。不能用氧气罐。

yingyinNormal.en: We do. We're gonna go to my son's house. Well, good. So, Kate, I just need a few more things for your intake forms. Is that your current weight?
yingyinNormal.zh: 是的。我们要去我儿子家。很好，凯特，关于你的初诊表，我还有些问题要补充。这是你当前的体重吗？

sense_info_list.en: an amount of food, air, or another substance taken into the body

examination_example.sentence: That is before we look for the space to grow the grains, sugars, seeds and oils that provide us with our current calorie <highlight>intake</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在此之前，我们找地方来种植谷物，糖，种子和油，为我们提供我们目前的卡路里摄入。

examination_example.sentence: To be fair, the FSA says it is not telling people to cut out roast foods entirely, but to reduce their lifetime <highlight>intake</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 公平地说，英国食品和药物管理局表示，并不是要让人们完全不吃烤肉，而是要减少他们一生的摄入量。

examination_example.sentence: If my training intensity remains the same, but I'm constantly hungry and dropping weight, this is a sign that I need to increase my daily caloric <highlight>intake</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果我的训练强度保持不变，但我经常感到饥饿和体重下降，这表明我需要增加每日热量摄入。

sense_info_list.en: an act of taking something into the body

sense_info_list.en: an amount of food, air, or another substance taken into the body

examination_example.sentence: According to a recent study, both the size and consumption habits of our eating companions can influence our food <highlight>intake</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据最近的一项研究，我们的饮食伙伴的体型和食用习惯都会影响我们的食物摄入量。

examination_example.sentence: When we choose a large spoon over a smaller one, total <highlight>intake</highlight>(摄入) jumps by 14 percent.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我们优先选择大勺子而不是小勺子时，总摄入量增长了14%。

sense_info_list.en: an amount of food, air, or another substance taken into the body

examination_example.sentence: The study found that vegetable <highlight>intake</highlight> if the children who grew their own produce increased greatly across the year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究发现，如果孩子种植自己的农产品，那么他们的年蔬菜摄入量会大大增加。

examination_example.sentence: New research suggests that a gardening program in schools can increase children's vegetable <highlight>intake</highlight> (摄入量).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 新的研究表明，学校的园艺项目可以增加儿童的蔬菜摄入量。

examination_example.sentence: For children, growing their own food is a powerful tool to increase their <highlight>intake</highlight> of the food.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对孩子们来说，自己种植食物是增加食物摄入量的有力工具。
